article.headline: North Texas 90, Florida Intl 81
article.story: DENTON, Texas (AP) -- Kendrick Davis scored 20 points and Isaac Hines added 19, including three 3-pointers, to lead North Texas to a 90-81 victory over Florida International on Thursday night. Davis hit 5-of-10 from the field and Hines 4-of-6. North Texas (9-5, 2-1 Sun Belt) hit 34-of-43 free throws in a foul-plagued game that saw two Florida International players foul out and four others each called for four fouls. Both teams had players called for technicals. Davis and Hines each hit eight free throws. Elvis Lora scored 19 points, including four 3-pointers, for Florida International (3-12, 0-3). Ivan Almonte added 15 points and had 11 rebounds. North Texas led 42-27 at the half. The Mean Green shot 41 percent from the field to 43 percent for the Panthers.
